Issues.Body:
### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

platform-server

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

It seems server-side rendered html not removed and just put client-side rendered html at the same position. 

It doesn't show any hydration error and just duplicate rendering. 

In PC project,
<img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7777929/233043151-02287c7a-e389-45a6-b12b-574a36b37734.png" width=200> 
In captured image, above one is server-side rendered html and below one is client-side rendered html. 

- use `ngSwitch + ngSwitchCase + ngSwitchDefault` directive
- node tree: `ng-container` > 2 parallel `ng-container + ngIf` > `dozen of small components`
- partially use `ng-template` with `if - else ng-container`
- list item for loop : `ngFor` + `trackBy` + `let i = index`

In Mobile project,
<img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7777929/233044109-bee75103-1c38-4f10-8bdb-98716edb8336.png" width=200> 
In captured image, left one is server-side rendered html and right is client-side rendered html. 

- not use `ngSwitch` related syntax
- node tree: `ng-container` > div > `ng-container` > `a tag with directive component` > 6 parallel ng-container > small components & div markup 
- list item for loop : `ngFor` + `trackBy` + `let i = index`


IF someone can give us similar cases or hints for reproduction, please give the information. 

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

Please wait for moment. i'm trying to reproduce it. it has no hydration error and two markup condition is quite complex. Its components consist of 20+ small-size components so its complexity is quite larger than other hydration error case. 

### Please provide the exception or error you saw

```true
No error message in console & our unit test codes.
```


